\section{THEOREMS}
The theorems required are the ``pod'' laws.
\subsection{Properties of the Ordering Alone}
=THDOC
req_thm(Û"dy_less_irrefl_thm"Ý, ([],
	¬µ x· ³ x dy_less x®);
req_thm(Û"dy_less_antisym_thm"Ý, ([],
	¬µ x y· ³ (x dy_less y ± y dy_less x)®);
req_thm(Û"dy_less_trans_thm"Ý, ([],
	¬µ x y z· x dy_less y ± y dy_less z ´ x dy_less z®);
req_thm(Û"dy_less_trich_thm"Ý, ([],
	¬µ x y· ³ x = y ´ x dy_less y ² y dy_less x®);
=DESCRIBE
Taken together, these four theorems say that
=INLINEFT
dy_less
=TEX
\ is a linear ordering on the set of positive dyadic rationals.
=ENDDOC
\subsection{Properties of Multiplication Alone}
=THDOC
